PN,41602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1779027073
OL,3,CPrivate school teacher stRuck off
OL,4,Cafter telling pupil she is 'Premier
OL,5,CLeague'
OL,7,FThe 48-year-old had also been
OL,8,Fappointed to the roles of assistant
OL,9,Fhead of Year 11 and head of house.
OL,11,FA misconduct hearing was told that Mr
OL,12,FSmith had become "increasingly close"
OL,13,Fto a pupil on a school trip and had
OL,14,Fengaged in regular one-to-one
OL,15,Fconversations with her.
OL,17,FIt was said that, following their
OL,18,Freturn from the trip, he exchanged
OL,19,Fseveral WhatsApp messages with her.
OL,26,@tD@ROUtD@eO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1779027073
OL,3,CPrivate school teacher stRuck off
OL,4,Cafter telling pupil she is 'Premier
OL,5,CLeague'
OL,7,FIn one message, seen by the Teaching
OL,8,FRegulation Agency's professional
OL,9,Fconduct panel, Mr Smith said to the
OL,10,Fgirl: "So, today I've seen a lot of my
OL,11,Ffavourite people and done some fun
OL,12,Fthings but I would have swapped it all
OL,13,Ffor a cup of milo, a game of spoons
OL,14,Fand just being silly with you."
OL,16,FIn another, he told the student she
OL,17,Fwas "Premier League and one of my
OL,18,Ffavourite people on the planet".
OL,26,@rD@GOUvD@_O]yD@EOUzD@_O]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1779027073
OL,3,CPrivate school teacher stRuck off
OL,4,Cafter telling pupil she is 'Premier
OL,5,CLeague'
OL,7,FMr Smith also told the girl that he
OL,8,Fwas "really proud" of her before
OL,9,Freferring to her as the best "hoody
OL,10,Fstealer", "bracelet addict", and "Mona
OL,11,FLisa friend", among other names.
OL,13,FIn his evidence to the panel, the PE
OL,14,Fteacher acknowledged that his messages
OL,15,Fat times were "too friendly and over
OL,16,Ffamiliar, but he thought it was due to
OL,17,Fspending 16/17 hours a day with
OL,18,Fsomeone".
OL,26,@pD@EOUpD@RO]qD@^OUrD@HO]rD@KOUrD@[O]rD@
OL,26,AbOUsD@LO]wD@OOUzD@HO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1779027073
OL,3,CPrivate school teacher stRuck off
OL,4,Cafter telling pupil she is 'Premier
OL,5,CLeague'
OL,7,FIt was said that in his written
OL,8,Fstatement, Mr Smith stated he had gone
OL,9,Fthrough the messages and agreed they
OL,10,Fwere unprofessional and "blurred the
OL,11,Flines between what is acceptable and
OL,12,Fnot".
OL,14,FThe girl, who cannot be named for
OL,15,Flegal reasons, also told the
OL,16,Fmisconduct hearing that on the journey
OL,17,Fhome from the school trip, she told Mr
OL,18,FSmith she was going to sleep and he
OL,19,Fsaid she could put her legs over him.
OL,26,@rD@YOUtD@DO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1779027073
OL,3,CPrivate school teacher stRuck off
OL,4,Cafter telling pupil she is 'Premier
OL,5,CLeague'
OL,7,FIt was said that the teacher then
OL,8,F"rubbed" and "touched" the pupil's
OL,9,Fthigh with his hands, an allegation
OL,10,Fwhich Mr Smith "categorically" denied
OL,11,Fbut the panel found proven.
OL,13,FThe panel also found that Mr Smith had
OL,14,Fphotographs of the student, bought her
OL,15,Fa fabric bracelet, and exchanged
OL,16,Fpersonal mobile telephone numbers with
OL,17,Fone or more pupils.
OL,19,FIn October 2023, Mr Smith was arrested
OL,20,Fby the police on suspicion of sexual
OL,21,Fassault and suspended from the school.
OL,26,@pD@AOUpD@HO]pD@NOUpD@VO]rD@POUrD@^O]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1779027073
OL,3,CPrivate school teacher stRuck off
OL,4,Cafter telling pupil she is 'Premier
OL,5,CLeague'
OL,7,FHowever, in December of that year, the
OL,8,Fpolice investigation was closed with
OL,9,Fno further action.
OL,11,FThat month, the teacher resigned from
OL,12,Fthe school, which costs around #18,000
OL,13,Fa year for senior students in year
OL,14,Fseven to year 11.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1779027073
OL,3,CPrivate school teacher stRuck off
OL,4,Cafter telling pupil she is 'Premier
OL,5,CLeague'
OL,7,FThe panel found that the teacher's
OL,8,Fconduct "involved serious and repeated
OL,9,Ffailures to maintain proper
OL,10,Fprofessional boundaries with a pupil
OL,11,Fand a failure to act in accordance
OL,12,Fwith safeguarding expectations,
OL,13,Frequirements and responsibilities".
OL,15,FThe report added: "The panel
OL,16,Fconsidered that these matters
OL,17,Fseriously undermined the standards
OL,18,Fexpected of a teacher and he sought to
OL,19,Fexploit his position of trust."
OL,26,@pD@IOUuD@bO]wD@SOU{D@_O]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41609
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1779027073
OL,3,CPrivate school teacher stRuck off
OL,4,Cafter telling pupil she is 'Premier
OL,5,CLeague'
OL,7,FSome of the other allegations made
OL,8,Fagainst the teacher were found not
OL,9,Fproven.
OL,11,FMr Smith has now been prohibited from
OL,12,Fteaching indefinitely.
OL,14,FHe can apply for the prohibition order
OL,15,Fto be set aside but not until 2029,
OL,16,Fand he has a right of appeal at the
OL,17,FHigh Court.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G9/10
